(1628, 204, '_page_module_6_image_right', 'field_5c8673b6298fb'),
(1629, 204, 'page_module_6_content_left', '<h3><strong>4-6 MONTHS</strong>\r\nFirst Solids</h3>\r\nOnce you get your pediatrician\'s green light to start solids, those first bites are exciting. Don’t forget to capture your child’s unforgettable expressions to all the new textures, tastes and sensations. Start slow, you actually do not need a ton of new equipment, just a few basics to help your child transition to solid foods. Every child is different, so be sure to respond appropriately to your baby’s cue. Happy feeding!'),
(1630, 204, '_page_module_6_content_left', 'field_5c8673c4298fc'),
(1631, 204, 'page_module_7_anchor_text', '4-8 MONTHS'),
(1632, 204, '_page_module_7_anchor_text', 'field_5c867562a11ef'),
(1633, 204, 'page_module_7_anchor_id', '4_8_months'),
(1634, 204, '_page_module_7_anchor_id', 'field_5c867567a11f0'),
(1635, 204, 'page_module_7_anchor', ''),
(1636, 204, '_page_module_7_anchor', 'field_5c867546a11ed'),
(1637, 204, 'page_module_7_image_left', '174'),
(1638, 204, '_page_module_7_image_left', 'field_5c86755fa11ee'),
(1639, 204, 'page_module_7_content_right', '<h3><strong>4-8 MONTHS</strong>\r\nSitting Up Independently</h3>\r\nAnd all of a sudden, your baby has a new perspective on the world – with that also comes a little bit more independence. Tummy time will have strengthened his neck, back and stomach, allowing him to make this remarkable achievement.\r\n\r\nNow that he can sit independently, leaving his hands free to explore, what will be the first thing he reaches for? After your baby accomplishes this milestone, crawling is right around the corner! Exciting times are ahead.'),
(1640, 204, '_page_module_7_content_right', 'field_5c867582a11f1'),
(1641, 204, 'page_module_8_anchor_text', '1-2 YEARS'),
(1642, 204, '_page_module_8_anchor_text', 'field_5c86767726493'),
(1643, 204, 'page_module_8_anchor_id', '1_2_years'),
(1644, 204, '_page_module_8_anchor_id', 'field_5c86767c26494'),
(1645, 204, 'page_module_8_anchor', ''),
(1646, 204, '_page_module_8_anchor', 'field_5c86767126492'),
(1647, 204, 'page_module_8_image_right', '181'),
(1648, 204, '_page_module_8_image_right', 'field_5c86768726495'),
(1649, 204, 'page_module_8_content_left', '<h3><strong>1 YEAR</strong>\r\nFirst Steps</h3>\r\nThey go from rolling over and sitting up, to crawling and standing all by themselves, and before you know it they’re actually taking their very first steps. You can’t believe your eyes. They’re really doing it! To see them actually take those first steps and then to gaze at their little face filled with awe and delight – what an experience!\r\n\r\nThis marks the beginning of a new and exciting stage – baby’s new self-sufficiency and mobility will lead her to explore endlessly with constant movement and falling – so much falling. This is a good time to introduce the concept of limits. Teach your baby that freedom comes with boundaries. It will help protect them from dangerous objects and situations – ready or not, here they come!'),
(1650, 204, '_page_module_8_content_left', 'field_5c86769026496'),
(1651, 204, 'page_module_9_anchor_text', ''),
(1652, 204, '_page_module_9_anchor_text', 'field_5c86780e60ad0'),
(1653, 204, 'page_module_9_anchor_id', ''),
(1654, 204, '_page_module_9_anchor_id', 'field_5c86781260ad1'),
(1655, 204, 'page_module_9_anchor', ''),
(1656, 204, '_page_module_9_anchor', 'field_5c8677a160acf'),
(1657, 204, 'page_module_9_image_left', '183'),
(1658, 204, '_page_module_9_image_left', 'field_5c86781760ad2'),
(1659, 204, 'page_module_9_content_right', '<h3><strong>1.5 - 2+ YEARS</strong>\r\nBig Kid’s Bed</h3>\r\nThis is one giant leap for your little one. A new bed means more freedom for you and your toddler – and also new rules, new setup and new routines. New big boy or big girl bed – check! Bed rail so little one doesn’t fall off the bed – check! New favorite sheets – check! Nightlight, bedtime books, pillows and stuffed animals – check, check, check, check! All of these items will help make the transition smooth.\r\n\r\nAnd also once the bars of the crib are gone, you will need to ensure the entire space is safe, so be aware of what needs to be childproofed, perhaps some furniture or items should be secured or removed from the room entirely.'),
(1660, 204, '_page_module_9_content_right', 'field_5c86781f60ad3'),
(1661, 204, 'page_module_10_anchor_text', '2+ YEARS'),
(1662, 204, '_page_module_10_anchor_text', 'field_5c8678e1edbb1'),
