(2969, 303, 'page_module_2_content_left', 'From the very moment you leave the hospital carrying your precious little newborn, you may have the feeling that you can’t really believe that the baby is actually here! This very tiny, really fragile baby is going to sit behind you in the car and they’re coming home with you.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>"Is this car seat in right? Did I buy the right kind? Is the belt too loose? Is he safe? Is he comfortable? Are we really prepared for this?”</em></strong>\r\n\r\nThese will be the first questions in your mind followed by about a million other questions throughout each day of new parenthood. Your daily routines will have forever changed. The days and months to come will be a steep learning curve filled with more worry and amazement than you have ever experienced.\r\n\r\nEach day brings new adventures and challenges. Being well-prepared to receive your newborn at home will make your first days at home together a little less overwhelming so that you can really savor those first powerful bonding moments.'),
(2970, 303, '_page_module_2_content_left', 'field_5c863d1ee27f1'),
(2971, 303, 'page_module_2_image_right', '132'),
(2972, 303, '_page_module_2_image_right', 'field_5c8638f94746e'),
(2973, 303, 'page_module_2_content_right', '<h3><strong>0-3 DAYS</strong>\r\nFirst Night at Home</h3>\r\nYes, you are now solely responsible for another person\'s life – and with no baby manual it may seem incredibly intimidating.\r\n\r\nDo your research well ahead of time, and hopefully, it will make that first night home a breeze for everyone. Very soon you will realize you survived that first night. And the second. And in a flash your baby will be a little toddler zipping happily around the house.'),
(2974, 303, '_page_module_2_content_right', 'field_5c863d38e27f2'),
(2975, 303, 'page_module_3_content', '<h3><strong>2 WEEKS</strong>\r\nIt’s Tub Time</h3>\r\nOnce baby\'s umbilical cord stump has fallen off, she\'s ready for a bath in her baby tub. Surprisingly, choosing a bathtub and personal care products isn\'t always straightforward.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>"Should the tub have a newborn support? Is the tub the right size for your baby? What are the procedures for bathtime? What should the water temperature be? Which personal care products are suitable and have less chemicals?"</em></strong>\r\n\r\nThe bath time routine is great for bonding as it provides a distraction-free routine to slow down and interact physically and emotionally with your baby.'),
